postcontent:
New, never used

The 3-15x50 Tactical Riflescope (Matte Black) from Weaver has been specially engineered for tactical applications. It has been manufactured to the strictest tolerances in order to perform in the harshest environments. The 3-15x50 Tactical riflescope is waterproof, fogproof and shockproof. It has a 30mm, single piece tube construction. This riflescope is endowed with a Mil-Dot reticle and has fully multicoated lenses that contribute to the brightness and contrast of the optics. Locating the reticle in the first focal plane allows the size of the pattern to increase as the magnification is increased. This is preferred by many tactical groups for use as a point of aim and as a means of measurement.

The side focus feature allows parallax adjustment to keep the reticle and target aligned regardless of the shooters head position. An extra-hard coating on the exterior lens surfaces protects the optics from the scratches and abrasions that all too often occur in the rough and tumble world of tactical endeavors. With a comfortable eye relief of approximately 4 inches and a ¼ MOA click value for the windage and elevation turret adjustments, this riflescope is provisioned with all the features required for serious tactical work. This is a serious glass for serious situations.

30 mm tube

One-piece construction

Argon purged to eliminate internal fogging

Reset-to-zero turrets allow consistently accurate and precise target acquisition

Waterproof, shockproof and fogproof provide rugged and durable protection to the scope

Powerful 5 times magnification to move quickly from a wider to a more defined field of view

Reticle located in the first focal plane allows the size of the pattern to increase as the magnification is increased

Fully multicoated optics: multiple layers on all air to glass surfaces for a brighter, higher-contrast image with less eyestrain

Side focus parallax adjustment provides compensation for the shooters head movement as it affects the apparent movement of the target relative to the reticle

The Mil-Dot reticle is the standard reticle used by the US Army and Marine Corps that enables long range distance calculations. A series of dots on the cross hairs gives the shooter the ability to judge bullet drop and the proper hold over for accurate long range shot placement

title: For Sale:  PTR-91 GI with hardcase, mags, factory upgrades, accessories, and spare parts
postcontent:
PTR-91 GI Special Edition (includes OD green furniture) with 18" barrel, chambered in .308 Winchester. This particular rifle has been fitted with a wide OD green handguard and enlarged charging handle, the original slim handguard and charging handle are included. The standard HK flash hider is included and removable if you wish to attach a different muzzle device. A Picatinny scope rail has been welded to the top of the receiver by the PTR factory, which included re-Parkerizing the rifle. Also included are the factory hard case, six 20-round aluminum magazines, one 10-round aluminum magazine, as well as spare small parts for the rear diopter sight (springs, bearings, screws, and lock washers - lose one of these while adjusting windage and you'll understand why).

I've owned this rifle just under a year now, and have fired 339 rounds of 150gr .308 Winchester ball through it. The manual recommends a break-in period of 200-300 rounds, but I have not experienced a malfunction of any kind thus far, and have kept the rifle clean and lubricated throughout. This past March I sent the rifle to the manufacturer to have them weld a Picatinny/1913 scope rail to the receiver since claw mount options are iffy, expensive, or both; they attached the rail and re-Parkerized the rifle while it was there, but I have not yet mounted any sort of optic to the rifle.

I am asking $1200 for the package, and will meet you at the location of your choice - Knob Creek Range in West Point or TG&G off of Newburg Road are my go-to locations for face to face sales and purchases, and I will provide a bill of sale / receipt.
